##Zhongshan Hospital to Wuhan Medical Team Leader: Do not want my team members to say too many brave words

Wechat media-fox

Features, for those who insist on serious reading options. Sohu News Extreme Day studio.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
ABSTRACT: As of February 17, more than 32,000 medical and nursing staff have supported Hubei Province to realize the goal of "collecting all revenues and treating all diseases" . On February 7, a team of 136 people led by Zhu Zhuzhuzhuowen, the deputy director of the Zhongshan Hospital affiliated to Fudan University and leader of one of the medical teams, was transferred to Hubei Province. A day later, they took over the two-storey wards of the East Hospital of Wuhan University People's Hospital, specializing in the treatment of critically ill patients. He notes that the disease is still a mystery, with many unknowns, but that there are ways to target it, based on past experience. "We are highly trained medical professionals. Please believe in our responsibility, our sense of mission and our knowledge, and we will do the best we can. "

By Zhou Hang

Editor | Wang Shan

After more than 10 days of support in Wuhan, the medical team of Shanghai Zhongshan Hospital laid down many rules, the most important one being safety first.

As team leader, Zhu's first instruction was to wear N95 masks at Wuhan airport and avoid touching anything inside.

Zhu Zhuzhuzhuowen believe that with the top level of colleagues in the country can do a good job, but the safety of the entire medical team, he is responsible for this team, by the whole team to participate.

Upon arrival in Wuhan, the hospital was assigned to the East Hospital of Wuhan University People's Hospital. The medical team of Zhongshan Hospital formulated infection control regulations and did not allow medical staff to take any risks.

In the early hours of February 11, the shift nurse found that the spare N95 masks were all but worn out, and the doctor on duty insisted that they not enter the contaminated area. Until the liaison officer brought the mask from the hotel more than ten kilometers away, and then handed over the shift.

Beyond security, there are many other rules, and the principles behind them are the same, respecting the dignity and basic needs of each individual. In order not to be overworked, the medical team stipulated that the working hours in the area of separation should not exceed four hours.

In the special period, Zhu also felt helpless because of the lack of nurses and cleaners, nurses had to feed and water the patients, wipe their bodies, clean up the dirt, clean the wards and carry the oxygen steel tanks, which also affected their expertise in intensive care.

What he and the hospital can do is to care for the staff as much as possible. From the size of a down jacket to the size of a family mask. On Valentine's Day, each team member was given a box of chocolates. One of the players had cake for his birthday.

"This is a very common thing, no need to exaggerate, " said Zhu, as straight and straight as ever, as if he didn't speak big words or expect his team to speak big words. "We are just doing our job. "

The following is collated from Zhu Zhuzhowen's presentation:

1

"My life is on track. "

Personally, this is the first time I've ever been out of the country. My family must be worried, but I'm a doctor, and I'm a leader, and I have nothing to say, so let's go.

In fact, before this, Shanghai has sent more than medical teams, our hospital also has many colleagues involved. We also know that as a national health commission hospitals, Wuhan if need support, we will definitely continue to want to, just do not know the time. But the size of the team, it was unexpected.

According to the requirements of the National Health Commission, the medical team to the front-line support to take 10 days of supplies, including protective materials and essential supplies. So we took it with us. Women's supplies like Sanitary Napkins are available in hospitals, except for personal carry-ons.

I didn't imagine the situation in Wuhan when I set out. We'll see when we get there. We'll adjust ourselves. At that time, said that supplies or local hospitals to provide, if insufficient, we must also timely replenishment of the rear. To find that, indeed, Wuhan did not run out of ammunition and food, People's Hospital is very hard in the preparation of supplies. The most important piece of protection, and we're using a lot of them right now.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wu People's hospital infection director Liu Zhichao to the medical team of the medical team to introduce the patient. Photo courtesy of Zhongshan Hospital on Wechat

There must still be a shortage at this stage. Materials are purchased, allocated, and donated, models, brands vary, we will be very careful inspection. Some things, such as masks, protective clothing, if we can not meet our requirements, or uncomfortable to use, then we bring their own.

The first night in Wuhan was tough, because you couldn't open the air conditioning, and the room was cold, but the heating equipment was replenished the next day.

Now, there's got to be a heating blanket for everyone, air heaters, oil-filled heaters, also known as heating pads, in every room. A while ago, everyone was given down jackets. Not just from the hospital, but from local and Shanghai donors. There are also UV lights sent from the back of the hotel corridor for room-by-room disinfection. I'm on the right track now.

The time relation, the material has some not considered, later replenishes. For example, full body protection and shoe covers, which were not considered before, were shipped in time. Another long time to wear protective products, face indentation, skin damage, the need for some paste, as well as water-moist things, the rear also timely call over.

In addition, including underwear, shoes, Shell, the hospital is well prepared. We've got hundreds of boxes of diapers in the hallway, but we're on a strict quarantine schedule, and we don't even need them.

We also have a large female team, with 100 nurses and only nine men. There are also quite a few women among the doctors. I can say that none of them were bothered by the lack of any supplies, which affected their work.

We didn't ask them to get their hair cut or anything. In fact, the nursing department has always had a policy on nurses'hair, not that it shouldn't be long, but long hair must be coiled inside the hat. Before setting out, some nurses go to the hospital barber shop to have their hair cut for convenience. Some I see now also a bit long, that dish is inside.

There are six administrative support staff in the medical team, four of whom have a clinical background. There are two others, one is the cadre of the Medical Service and the other is the cadre of the General Affairs Department. They are mainly responsible for the material support (receiving and sending) and many internal affairs.

For example, contact to determine the daily shuttle bus. I want the men to finish their work every day and return to their quarters as soon as possible. So the shuttle leaves on the morning shift, and starts at noon, and it goes back and forth every hour, basically, into the evening. Late at night, late at night. Shift dense, the driver is also hard, Wuhan high-tech zone, the People's Hospital gave great support.

Materials from the rear, large items are through the special line to the Wuchang Railway Station, also want to pick up, to the headquarters to apply for large vehicles, but sometimes no workers, we will drive the good people donated commercial vehicles, ant move. So there's no one to spare.

In addition, the Internet said that our hospital also brought a cook, security, which is a myth. We don't have room for a cook. What's with the security.

We get three meals a day from a hotel or a hospital. There's nothing wrong with the food. No taste. Is that team members may have irregular mealtimes. There's microwaves on both sides. Sometimes you just have to heat it up. It is hoped that continued traffic control will not have too great an impact on the supply of food, especially meat.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
From 21 p.m. to 7 a.m. the next day, the Zhongshan Hospital medical team provided supplies for the night shift. Photo: Public Account of Zhongshan Hospital on Wechat

2

More than 30 patients developed mild illness and three died

We took over the medical building of the People's Hospital on two floors, the original one floor is the cardiology ward, one floor is the neurology ward.

The East Hospital of the People's Hospital was very difficult to transform from a General Hospital to an Infectious Disease Hospital in a short period of time, from the earliest 200 fixed-point beds to the later 400, and now to 800 intensive care isolation wards.

After reconstruction, these wards can meet the basic requirements of the separation of two passages (medical staff passage and patient passage) in the three zones of infectious ward (clean area, contaminated area and semi-polluted area) .

Before we arrived, the ward had admitted new pneumonia patients, but many of them were mild cases, the doctor is also the former section of the doctor. When we came in, according to the command post, the mild cases were discharged, and only the severe cases were admitted later.

We now have a total of 80 beds under our care, and we currently have 70 patients, all of whom are critically ill, some of whom are critically ill.

Better patients can walk on their own, basic self-care life, some tests can also be done in the past, serious completely in bed can not move, has been on the breathing machine.

It's a combination of treatments. Such as oxygen therapy, antiviral drug, low-dose hormones, and, not to forget, increased nutrition, as well as "talk therapy" , which is words to comfort the patient as much as possible, so that they relax and have more confidence. The disease depends on the patient's immune system, and their state of mind is important.

To now (February 19) , a cumulative total of more than 30 to transfer to other places, but also three patients did not rescue over, unfortunately died. We have to analyze every case, discuss whether there's room for improvement in the future.

The disease we face this time is really dangerous, some patients with severe illness will suddenly deteriorate, sometimes simply did not expect such a change, is My colleague, the first to the Golden Pool Hospital to support the intensive care doctor Zhong Ming mentioned before the "Inflammation Storm" , now everyone is very familiar with this expression, but the specific treatment, or in the fumble.

There's another problem. There are no nurses, and there are very few cleaners. Our nurses do a lot of cleaning, nursing, and even carrying oxygen cylinders. Nurses, doctors, are selected to have a professional elite, down-to-earth ability. But that shouldn't be the norm, and that's something we have to face.

Lack of oxygen supply is also a common problem in Wuhan. The original design of the wards was not intended for patients who needed oxygen on such a large scale.

Every critically ill patient needs oxygen, and the only difference is that some need it intermittently, some need it continuously, some need it with a mask, and some need to be intubated. Right now it's replenished with oxygen tanks, so the nurses are struggling.

In addition, we as an ICU, to treat some critically ill patients, in fact, also need a complete ICU configuration, has been equipped with a lot of machines, but still not enough.

For example, different types of suction machine, some pipes, filters are not matched. Of course, these can not be in place in one step, in fact now than just came has been much better, but also continue to improve.

We brought in 30 doctors in 10 specialties, mainly respiratory, severe and infectious, as well as anesthesiology, emergency medicine, cardiology, neurology, nephrology, gastroenterology and, of course, nursing.

Medicine is professional, rigorous, we respect the law of medicine, on the basis of the existing, recognized principles of treatment, according to clinical conditions, diagnosis and treatment, because there are many unknown, so there must be exploratory practice in it.

What I want to emphasize about treatment is, first of all, this disease is a mystery, and there are a lot of unknowns, but we're not completely ignorant. After all, it is also a virus, clinical manifestations mainly in the lungs, there are also signs of invasion of other organs. Based on past experience, we still have some tools to target treatment.

Second, we are highly trained medical professionals, please believe in our sense of responsibility, please believe in our sense of mission and professional knowledge, we will do this work as best as possible.

A doctor came back from the quarantine area to treat a patient and took a nap on a chair in his office. Photo courtesy of Zhongshan Hospital on Wechat

3

"Our medics are brave,
But don't think a hero deserves to die."

"Our medics are brave,

But don't think a hero deserves to die."

I'm pretty much between the hotel and the station right now. Work Content, one is to ensure, one is to coordinate, such as communication with the rear demand, coordination of receiving goods from Shanghai and so on. Another team management, so far we have issued five circulars, the most important is infection control, stressed the safety of the regulations. There are also rules, such as don't go out.

In addition, in the Eastern Hospital of the People's Hospital, every two nights to hold a leadership meeting, the People's Hospital and several aid medical teams (from Xinjiang, Shaanxi, Sichuan, Liaoning, Shandong, etc.) together. Supplies, drug supplies, testing, medical procedures, professional consultation needs and so on, what special problems need to be solved together, together.

Like bedside films, how to make an appointment, how to do a test, how to get the report back, all kinds of details, we all ask. Seven medical teams here, medical principles are the same, but how much a little difference in clinical practice, need to communicate with the People's Hospital, there will be personalized arrangements. We all have the number of the People's Hospital now.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Every doctor works different hours, depending on the nature of the job, and everyone is on rotation. There's no need to stress that working the night shift is dedication. In fact, in Shanghai, we are also very hard.

In a word, the principle is to match one's own physical, mental, and mental abilities, and to do one's best to make fair arrangements. Do not require excessive consumption, such as in the quarantine area, several layers of gloves, full protective clothing, shoe covers, etc. , can not eat, toilet, working environment and normal completely different, operation is beginning to be strange. As a result, we have a strict policy that no nurse in the quarantine area should be on duty for more than four hours.

If anyone experiences any discomfort, such as a common fever, or a high-intensity, continuous work in a quarantined area, or a nurse becomes dehydrated and passes out, schedule a rest.

On our sixth day, we did an anonymous survey through a small program, asking about accommodation, food, shifts, and transportation. Everyone is generally satisfied. Someone asked if they could send some protective equipment to their home in Shanghai, and I immediately reported it to the head office, which said that it was perfectly possible to operate immediately and send some masks to each household.

There are also a number of personal issues that need to be resolved separately. For example, someone said, down jacket collar is too big, we let him find right away, peer-to-peer solution.

So far, we've lost three patients in two wards. For doctors and nurses of considerable seniority, death in itself is not a very terrible thing. But in this new environment, medical professionals need some counseling, some reassurance.

What I want to emphasize is, if you want to keep the health care workers relatively calm, you first have to think about what the hospital is offering them -- , whether they have adequate protection, whether the job is not impractical, and if they don't, then don't talk about psychological intervention.

Our staff are courageous in the sense that the disease is contagious and the response is challenging. But don't think that "hero" is worth dying for.

What's a hero? It doesn't make sense to save a patient's life without protective gear. Strictly speaking, injuries should not be, should be avoided.

Don't even go up in the air. To put it mildly, we're just moving from city to city, from hospital to hospital, but it's the same job, doctor to doctor, nurse to nurse. I've always felt it was our duty to save lives and prevent epidemics. I want you to get the job done, but only if it's safe.

We are not just talking about treating medical staff as human beings, we should treat everyone as human beings, especially patients, who need all-round, whole-body care, which is a very basic requirement of being a human being.

This kind of humane care also permeates in our ordinary dribs and drabs. For example, our health care workers give out fruit to patients, provide smartphones, and help with videos for the elderly and their families. In fact, without caring for the patient in these areas, our entire care package is incomplete.

These are also very natural things, there is no need to render anything. I don't like to talk big, and I don't want my players to talk big. People just respect the rules, follow the procedures, and do their jobs.
